MAPPING.DESCRIPTION: ITPR010874 - This mapping will update the Process control table to Completion status or report ready status based on the transaction type in the table once the insert to claim report table is successful Transaction type = 50, update process status to ‘C’ Transaction type = 51, Update process status to ‘R1’

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This SQ will get all rows that have the running status for Generate data process which is 'P1' and update it to Complete(C) and Ready for Send process status(R1)

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: Select RPT_PRCS_NB, RPT_PRCS_TYP_CD from $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSZ6020_RPT_PRCS_CNTL where RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD in ('$$PARM_RPT_RUN') with ur

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Transaction type = 50, update process status to ‘C’ complete status Transaction type = 51, Update process status to ‘R1’ ready for send data process
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Update the Process control table based on Process number
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: Upd_RPT_PRCS_CNTL

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This SQ will get all rows that have the running status for Generate data process which is 'P1' and update it to Complete(C) and Ready for Send process status(R1)

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Takes 9 variables and creates 9 separate rows of data. Used to populate the parameter file.

TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT B.RPT_PRCS_NB, B.STMT_ID, B.RPT_START_BILL_PRD, B.LAST_RBAT_BILL_PRD, B.RPT_TYP_CD, C.RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME, C.RBAT_ID FROM $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSZ6020_RPT_PRCS_CNTL B, $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSZ6015_RPT_CNTL_ID C WHERE C.RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME=B.RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME AND C.RPT_TYP_CD=B.RPT_TYP_CD AND B.RPT_PRCS_TYP_CD IN ($$PARM_RPT_PRCS_TYP) AND B.RPT_PRCS_STAT_CD IN ('$$PARM_RPT_RUN') with ur

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: RPS stage data count for the request

TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT count(*) as COUNT_RPS,$$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSRB335_RPT_CLM_STG.RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME as RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME, $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSRB335_RPT_CLM_STG.RPT_PRCS_NB as RPT_PRCS_NB FROM $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSRB335_RPT_CLM_STG group by $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSRB335_RPT_CLM_STG.RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME, $$MVS_DB2_OWNER.KSRB335_RPT_CLM_STG.RPT_PRCS_NB with ur;--

MAPPING.DESCRIPTION: 06/25 - This mapping generates claim level detail data for the requested client. Includes all rebated claims from APC for all active QTRs till the period requested along with the associated fields from RPS staging if the claim is available in RPS and All submitted claims that have the post adjusted and new invoice associated will be loaded.
MAPPING.NAME: m_RPS_RPT_Insert_Bal_TCLM_RPT_DETL

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This will filter claims based on whether the claim was rebated or if present in RPS claims stage table. All the rebated claims and matching RPS claims will be loaded.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: FIL_SUB_NO_RPS_DATA

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This will look up the RPS reporting claims stage table and get the required fields for loading into the claims reporting detail target.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_ACTIVE_RPS_STAGING

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This will count the number of rebated, submitted claims and reports for each client. It also does the data validation to make sure all claims trabnsactions from RPS staging are loaded into final table
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: AGG_BALANCE

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This will validate the claim counts against report count and will write out the paramater whether the validation succeeded or failed. The process will be aborted if the validation fails.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_BALANCE

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: making sure the rebated plus Summited count is equal to the overall count
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: v_COUNT_VALIDATION

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Get the count from Parameter file and match it with teh count from the Filter to make sure all RPS claims are available
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF(out_MATCH_COUNT<>v_RPS_COUNT,ABORT('Data Validation Error between APC and RPS'),'Data validation success')
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: v_DATA_VALIDATION

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: in_RPT_CLNT_SHORT_NME||' '||v_COUNT_VALIDATION||' For Process Number '||in_RPT_PRCS_NB|| ' along with '||v_DATA_VALIDATION
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: out_PARAMETER

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Source Filter
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: RPS.VAPC_DETAIL.PERIOD_ID BETWEEN '$$START_ACTIVE_QTR' AND '$$END_ACTIVE_QTR' AND RPS.VAPC_DETAIL.RBATE_ID IN ($$RBAT_IDs)

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: When no data from RPS it is defaulted to N
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: TRAN_TYP_CD

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Will get the value from APC only when RPS data is NULL
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: out_VAPC_PICO_NO

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This will filter claims based on whether the claim was rebated or if present in RPS claims stage table. All the rebated claims and matching RPS claims will be loaded.
INSTANCE.NAME: FIL_SUB_NO_RPS_DATA

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This will look up the RPS reporting claims stage table and get the required fields for loading into the claims reporting detail target.
INSTANCE.NAME: LKP_ACTIVE_RPS_STAGING

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This will count the number of rebated, submitted claims and reports for each client. It also does the data validation to make sure all claims trabnsactions from RPS staging are loaded into final table
INSTANCE.NAME: AGG_BALANCE

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This will validate the claim counts against report count and will write out the paramater whether the validation succeeded or failed. The process will be aborted if the validation fails.
INSTANCE.NAME: EXP_BALANCE
